25/08/2003
PODUJEVA, Serbia-Montenegro -- Stressing that the Podujeva region of southern Serbia is considered safe, KFOR announced plans to launch a third weapons collections programme in nearby Kosovo on 1 September.
KFOR says those who turn in illegal weapons during the month will be granted amnesty, with no questions asked.
In other news, Serbian Deputy Prime Minister Nebojsa Covic, who is also Belgrade's Co-ordinator for Kosovo, said on Sunday (24 August) that negotiations with Pristina could start within weeks.
Covic expressed cautious optimism about new UNMIK chief Harri Holkeri.
(Beta - 24/08/03;
Bota Sot - 23/08/03)
